  "notes": [
    "This pilot study demonstrates a high prevalence (58.7%) of reversible tactile hypoesthesia in patients with myofascial trigger points.",
    "The study suggests that trigger point injections can be used to distinguish myofascial pain from neuropathic pain based on the reversibility of tactile hypoesthesia.",
    "The mechanism proposed involves inhibition of the primary somatosensory cortex by nociceptive input from myofascial trigger points."
  ]
